lenders.loan_because:
312-671-1996 is a very important number to me as it holds a number of significant milestones in my life. 312-671-1996 happens to be my childhood phone number of where I grew up in the suburbs of Chicago, Illinois. I had always been a big fan of the Chicago Bulls and couldn’t help but watch every game when Michael Jordan was a member of the team. Jordan had a knack for taking that last big shot in the waning seconds of the game. He thrived under pressure and always wanted to be the one who beat the other team with his end of game heroics.

The number 312-671-1996 not only holds a near and dear place in my heart for where I grew up in Chicago, Illinois, but it’s also my lucky winning number. 312-671-1996 is my go to number when it comes to any lottery game and I have been lucky to win some money along the way. Everyone has their personal numbers that they will play or use for different circumstances. When it comes to the lottery, 312-671-1996 is my number. It has always been and will be forever.

People can be very superstitious when it comes to numbers. Numbers to me are just digits that follow one another in no sequential order whatsoever. 312-671-1996 might be my childhood phone number, a number for many that bears little meaning latter in life, but for me it sticks with me everyday. Nowadays, people don’t think of landline phone numbers anymore and they are becoming more and more caught up with mobile cell phones. I remember when I had to reach my parents, the only way I could was to call 312-671-1996 - my home phone. It’s crazy to think how far we’ve come from landline to mobile cell phones. I would think new home owners might shy away from putting in a landline. Is it truly necessary? Couldn’t a mobile phone suffice? More often than not, people take their calls on cell phones, so I could see why people might not need a landline phone.

312-671-1996 is a number that I will continue to use in certain situations and I don’t think I will ever forget it. The number brings back a lot of great memories and I’m sure it will only continue to provide more in the future.
